<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-01-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="84" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Baron <persName type="from">Riedl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Imperial and Royal Austro-Hungarian Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-01-17"><hi rend="italic">January
                                        17, 1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: Referring to our
                            last conversation on the Lattimer affair, I have the honor to inform you
                            that Mr. Robert D. Coxe is free to proceed to Washington January 18, 19,
                            20, 21,23, and 28.</p>
                        <p>You would very much oblige me by having me informed which of the days
                            aforesaid and what hour would be convenient to you for granting the
                            favor of an audience to Mr. Coxe.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Riedl.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>